#-Function--check.dependencies
  Function: check.dependencies
      Desc: check for script dependencies (programs, scripts, or functions).
  Synopsis: check.dependencies [-q|--quiet] name [...]
          : 	name				is the name of a program, script or function.
          : #X					:		-q|--quiet	do not print 'dependency-not-found' messages.
   Example: (( check.dependencies dirname ln )) && msgdie "Dependencies missing."
#-Function--check.dependencies------------------------------------------------
